    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-05T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="767"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/1234: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-05T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 5, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 5—4:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. American interests, Germany. Department’s 3222, December 24.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d767fn4">
                        <ref target="frus1943v01#pg_434">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1943, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 434</ref>.</note> Swiss note January 4
                    states Swiss Legation, Berlin, reports Minister Albrecht of German Foreign
                    Office stated December 31 not yet able comment reports concerned. Legal Section,
                    Foreign Office, has likewise been unable to so far give consideration this
                    matter. Appears for present to involve only threats in field political
                    propaganda <pb facs="1242" n="1228" xml:id="pg_1228"/> but not yet possible
                    verify degree to which these press radio statements correspond to attitude
                    German authorities.</p>
                <p>Swiss promise revert subject receipt Berlin’s detailed report. Repeated to
                    London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
